cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper proposes probabilistic model checking techniques for concurrent stochastic games based on Nash equilibria. The paper focuses on extending the temporal logic rPATL for reasoning about players with distinct quantitative goals, which relates to either the probability of an event occurring or a reward measure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper extends the temporal logic rPATL for reasoning about players with distinct quantitative goals, which suggests that it may belong to this sub-category.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper proposes probabilistic model checking techniques for concurrent stochastic games based on Nash equilibria, which suggests that it may belong to this sub-category.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents algorithms to synthesise strategies that are social welfare optimal Nash equilibria, which suggests that it may belong to this sub-category.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper applies its techniques to several case studies, including network protocols and robot navigation, which suggests that it may belong to this sub-category.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper implements its techniques in an extension of the PRISM-games tool, which suggests that it may belong to this sub-category.
